The paper discusses a framework for conducting multi-level studies of complex social systems using agent-based models and empirical data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on agent-based models and their use in simulating complex social systems, cs.MA is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they touch on different aspects of the paper's content, such as social networks, control systems, and the societal impact of computing.
